  "prompt": "How long does a high school basketball game usually last?",
  "response": "A typical high school basketball game in the United States generally consists of **four 8-minute quarters**, totaling **32 minutes of regulation play**. However, when you account for **halftime breaks**, **timeouts**, **official reviews**, and other stoppages, the **entire game usually lasts around 60 minutes (1 hour)** from start to finish.\n\n**Breakdown:**\n- **Regulation Time:** 4 quarters \u00d7 8 minutes each = 32 minutes\n- **Halftime:** Approximately 10-15 minutes\n- **Timeouts and Other Stoppages:** Can add an additional 20-25 minutes\n- **Overtime (if necessary):** Each overtime period is typically 4 minutes\n\nSo, under normal circumstances without overtime, you can expect a high school basketball game to take about **1 hour**. If the game is tied at the end of regulation, overtime periods will extend the total duration accordingly.\n\n**Note:** While these are standard guidelines based on the National Federation of State High School Associations (NFHS) rules, specific durations might vary slightly depending on the state or individual school district's regulations.",
